Who we are
We are IMG, which includes IMG Worldwide, LLC and affiliated entities. We are also part of Endeavor and may share data with its affiliated entities (“Endeavor”).
IMG is a global leader in sports, fashion, events and media. We manage some of the world’s greatest athletes and fashion icons; own and operate hundreds of live events annually; and are a leading independent producer and distributor of sports and entertainment media. We also specialize in licensing, sports training, and league development.
Like any company, we use a variety of third party businesses and partners to market and provide our Services to you. Some of those companies are part of Endeavor and some are third parties that we partner with or support our operations so we can provide the best experience to you.
How we collect information about you
Directly From You
You may provide us with personal information in a number of ways, such as when you:
Provide information to us via our websites, applications, and other digital channels by signing up, creating accounts (including using social media login), filling out forms, commenting, or otherwise engaging with our online services
Communicate with us by e-mail or phone
Subscribe to e-mails and/or newsletters
Report a problem or request support for any of our Services
Buy a ticket or merchandise from us online
Interact with our social media accounts
Participate in our contests, promotions, sweepstakes or surveys
Subscribe to IMG content online including using any of our online social media channels, official video or streaming partners
Attend any IMG event (e.g., ticket scanning, CCTV, and other on location interactions you may have with us
Information we collect from other sources
We work closely with third parties (for example, technical service providers, ticketing providers, promotions companies, advertising networks, analytics providers, and search information providers) and may receive information about you from them. Depending on the relationship and activity, they will provide us with certain information that will help us understand how you interact with IMG Services so we can tailor our marketing and provide better, more personalized Services to you. In some cases, third parties also provide us with information that helps us keep track of transactions, address technical or logistical issues, prevent fraud, or keep our community safe from security threats.
We may also receive and display information and content which you make publicly available on your social media account when you use social media logins for our Services, post using one of our promoted hashtags, or interact with any of our content (such as contests).
Some of our key partners, who we receive data from and may share some data with include:
Event partners and sponsors, who we work with to host premier events around the world
Media and Digital Content partners, who we partner with to share exclusive content, including PPV packages of IMG events
E-commerce platforms and services, which provide merchandise to fans around the world
Ticket sellers around the world who sell tickets to IMG events
Venues which host IMG events and provide various marketing, advertising, customer support, and security services related to IMG events
We may also receive and display information and content which you make publically available on your social media account, such as when you post using one of our promoted hashtags.
